parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities. The malfunction can also result in extended stopping distances, increasing the risk of rear-end collisions.
symptoms: The ABS light on the dashboard illuminates
the brake pedal pulsates or goes to the floor
the vehicle experiences delayed or erratic braking
the vehicle loses control at low speeds on wet or slippery surfaces
and the brakes lock up or vibrate when applied.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel Tank Leakage and Rusted Brake and Fuel Lines
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Fuel tank leakage can cause fires, explosions, and accidents, while rusted brake and fuel lines can lead to brake failure, loss of vehicle control, and accidents.
symptoms: Gas smell or fumes coming from the gas tank area
fuel leaking from the tank
fuel tank cracking
brake lines and fuel lines critically rusted
soft or spongy brake pedal
loss of brake power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Fuel pump failure can cause the vehicle to stall, leading to accidents, and can also cause fires or explosions due to electrical malfunctions.
symptoms: Vehicle stalls
power steering and brakes stop working
fuel pump failure
blown EMC fuse
strong gas smell from the rear of the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction can cause various electrical components to fail, leading to safety issues, such as stalling, loss of headlights, and battery drain, which can increase the risk of accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Rear compartment air blower not stopping
dashboard lights not turning off
headlights going out
battery malfunctioning
stalling
electrical short
and ignition switch failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake hydraulic control unit can cause internal fluid leaks, leading to brake failure, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Brake failure
stalling while traveling at high speeds.
